## 22. Issues & Findings

### 🔴 Critical — Sensitive Data Exposure

| Issue | Endpoint | Risk |
|-------|----------|------|
| **Plaintext password in response** | `POST /api/accounts/staff/{id}/reset_password/` | Returns `{detail: "Password reset to {username}1234"}` — exposes password in API response, logs, network traces |
| **Plaintext credentials in response** | `POST /api/students/{id}/approve/` | Returns `{credentials: {idn, password}}` — initial password visible in response |
| **Debug print statements** | `LoginSerializer.validate()` | `print(f"DEBUG: Login attempt for username: {attrs.get('username')}")` — leaks login attempts to stdout |
| **`import` inside class body** | [StaffManagementViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/accounts/views.py#58-96) | `from rest_framework.decorators import action` on line 88 is inside the class body — unusual pattern, may cause issues |

### 🟠 High — Missing Permission Restrictions

| Issue | Endpoint | Impact |
|-------|----------|--------|
| **No role-based permissions** | [PaymentViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/finance/views.py#9-64) (CRUD) | Any authenticated user can create payments — should be `IsCashier \| IsAdmin` |
| **No role-based permissions** | [SectionViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/sections/views.py#11-152) (CRUD) | Any authenticated user can create/update/delete sections — should be `IsRegistrar \| IsAdmin` |
| **No role-based permissions** | [ScheduleViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/scheduling/views.py#14-189) (CRUD + assign + publish) | Any authenticated user can create/publish schedules — should be `IsDean \| IsAdmin` |
| **No role-based permissions** | [StudentEnrollmentViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/students/views.py#316-396) (CRUD) | Any authenticated user can modify enrollments — missing write restrictions |
| **Overly permissive** | [StudentViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/students/views.py#14-315) (update/delete) | Only `IsAuthenticated` for PUT/PATCH/DELETE on students |
| **Manual permission check** | [returning_student](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/students/views.py#186-233) action | Uses inline `if not (role == 'ADMIN' or ...)` instead of proper `permission_classes` |

### 🟡 Medium — Inconsistent Naming

| Pattern | Endpoints | Issue |
|---------|-----------|-------|
| URL casing inconsistency | `/pick-regular/` uses kebab-case but `/status_matrix/`, `/available_slots/`, `/auto_advise/` use snake_case | Pick one convention |
| `/mark-read/` vs `/mark_all_read/` | Notifications | Kebab vs. snake_case within the same ViewSet |
| Router prefix `r''` (empty) | [AuditLogViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/auditing/views.py#19-60), [RoomViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/facilities/views.py#6-13), [NotificationViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/notifications/views.py#8-43), [TermViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/terms/views.py#8-21), [SectionViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/sections/views.py#11-152), [ScheduleViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/scheduling/views.py#14-189) | Registered with empty prefix — works but creates less descriptive API root |
| Plural vs singular | `api/auditing/` (singular-ish) vs `api/academics/programs/` (plural) | Inconsistent resource naming |

### 🟡 Medium — Missing Validation

| Issue | Endpoint | Detail |
|-------|----------|--------|
| No body validation | `GET /reports/cor/` | `student_id` is compared as string but stored as integer — potential type mismatch |
| No serializer for writes | `professors/{id}/subjects/`, `professors/{id}/availability/`, `professors/{id}/assign_subjects/` | Read raw `request.data` without serializer validation |
| No serializer for writes | `scheduling/assign/`, `scheduling/pick-regular/`, `scheduling/pick-irregular/`, `scheduling/publish/` | All read raw `request.data` |
| No serializer for writes | `students/{id}/approve/`, `students/{id}/toggle_regularity/`, `students/{id}/returning_student/`, `students/manual_add/` | All read raw `request.data` |
| No serializer for writes | `sections/generate/`, `sections/{id}/transfer/` | Raw `request.data` usage |
| No serializer for writes | `grades/approvals/`, `grades/crediting/`, `grades/submission/`, `grades/resolution/` (most actions) | Many custom actions bypass serializer validation |
| `fields = '__all__'` | [ScheduleSerializer](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/scheduling/serializers.py#4-16), [SectionStudentSerializer](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/sections/serializers.py#40-47) | Exposes all model fields including potentially internal ones |
| Broad exception handling | Multiple endpoints | `except Exception as e: return Response({"error": str(e)})` may expose internal error details |

### 🟢 Low — Undocumented Endpoints

| Endpoint | Issue |
|----------|-------|
| DRF Router API Root endpoints | Each `DefaultRouter` generates a browsable API root (e.g., `api/academics/`) — undocumented |
| Django Admin | `admin/` — always accessible, default Django admin |
| `api/grades/advising/` CRUD | [AdvisingViewSet](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/grades/views.py#17-86) has a `serializer_class = GradeSerializer` but unclear if standard CRUD (list/create/update/delete) is intended beyond the custom actions |
| `api/grades/approvals/` CRUD | [AdvisingApprovalViewSet(viewsets.ViewSet)](file:///c:/Users/Administrator/Desktop/richwell-potal/backend/apps/grades/views.py#88-135) — no standard CRUD, only custom actions. But DRF ViewSet still exposes the API root |

